# Force LF on checkout for every text file, on every platform.
#
# Why: the hook scripts (*.sh, session-start, run-hook.cmd) and the injected
# SESSION-PREAMBLE.md are consumed by Unix tooling (bash, /usr/bin/env, WSL,
# Git Bash). A Windows clone uses Git's default core.autocrlf=true, which would
# rewrite them to CRLF — breaking script execution under WSL/Unix
# (`/usr/bin/env: 'bash\r': No such file or directory`) and putting stray \r into
# the injected context. Normalizing to LF everywhere keeps every checkout correct.
* text=auto eol=lf
